<TITLE> Dhaka, Delhi renew water transit treaty </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 24 (Bdnews24.com)Bangladesh and India renewed the Protocol on Inland Water Transit and Travel for two years on Tuesday. "The renewal of the prevailing water transit agreement will have the same terms as before," said shipping minister Afsarul Amin earlier in the day. "The agreement has been in force for many years, but it has to be updated and modernised if Bangladesh is to reap further benefits from the arrangement," said the minister. Acting shipping secretary Mohammed Masud Elahi and visiting Indian additional shipping secretary Vijay Chhibber signed the agreement on behalf of their respective governments, at the Sonargaon Hotel. The agreement was signed between the two nations in 1972, to be renewed every two years. bd
